The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Workers protest Bata move

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Calcutta, Feb. 19: Bata India employees have vowed to take on the management for closing some 20 shops in the city. Employees have said they would not let anyone other than the employees of these particular shops to open the shops.

 We will take the agitation route and also legal recourse. If the management follows this whimsical method, they will have to face the consequences, Robin Mazumder of Bata Shop Employees Union said.

 The Bata management today put out a public notice saying that Bata India has terminated 11 managers and employees working under it for not following the companys directive to keep the shop open till 9 in the evening.

 It also suspended the permanent employees of Bata stores located at Grand Hotel, Hindustan Park, Lindsay Street, College Street and Sealdah. The Bata management has taken control of these shops.




